        "subject": "LU-19496 kfilnd: Fix error handling in DMA mapping",
        "message": "LU-19496 kfilnd: Fix error handling in DMA mapping\n\nRefactor kfilnd_tn_set_sgl_buf() to improve error handling and code\nclarity:\n\n- Add function documentation describing parameters, behavior, and\n  return values\n- Include network interface name in all error messages for better\n  debugging context\n- Add error handling for DMA mapping failures (both GPU and non-GPU\n  paths)\n- tn_sgt_mapped is now only set when the sg_table is successfully\n  mapped. kfilnd_tn_set_sgl_buf() will free the sg_table in the case\n  of error.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I6e28e606b84e1738c7cd7a516a8acb50a0f1b769\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61918\nReviewed-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander.boyko@hpe.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Ron Gredvig <ron.gredvig@hpe.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
